result.execSummary:
The defendant Stacey Ryan Hilario was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Stacey Ryan Hilario is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Stacey Ryan Hilario was found guilty of Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).
  • Stacey Ryan Hilario was found guilty of Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court reporter Teri Groves. Defendant in court, in custody with Attorney Ronald Gabriel Benavides.  Cecilia E DeMarco appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Stacey Ryan Hilario appeared by video means with Attorney. State motions the court to find all counts transactionally related. Atty Benavides responds. Court grants the request. Witness L.H. is duly sworn an testified. Direct by State. Venue established. Defendants identification challenged based Atty Benavides objection that States identification questions were unduly suggestive. State responds. Court will reserve ruling on identification. State continues with direct exam. Cross by Atty Benavides. Witness excused. Witness D.H. is duly sworn and testified. Direct by State. No cross exam. Witness is excused. State moves for bind over, reserves argument. Defense gives argument and requests a dismissal due to unduly suggestive identification procedure. State responds.  Court declines Atty Benavides request for dismissal.  Court offers defense the option of having preliminary hearing set-over and re-conducted at a future date when Stacey Ryan Hilario can be present in Court.  Atty Benavides declines set-over. Court overruled defense objection, finds good cause, and binds the DE over to Branch 13.
